snippet.textDisplay: First, I feel so bad for the families that lost loved ones on that helicopter.  And here, I feel very badly for Jerry West.  You can tell he genuinely loved Kobe like a son.  His heart is breaking.  Mr. West seems so genuine and real.  For his own personal fame and fortune, he seems like a very good-natured, caring man.  I also think about the Altobelli’s surviving 16 year old daughter.  Imagine losing your younger sister and your mom and dad all at once at such a young age!  How does that poor child recover from that?  She’s in high school and should be enjoying the fun of life with friends and family in a carefree environment.  I really pray for that child. snippet.textOriginal: First, I feel so bad for the families that lost loved ones on that helicopter.  And here, I feel very badly for Jerry West.  You can tell he genuinely loved Kobe like a son. I also think about the Altobelli’s surviving 16 year old daughter.  Imagine losing your younger sister and your mom and dad all at once at such a young age!  How does that poor child recover from that?  She’s in high school and should be enjoying the fun of life with friends and family in a carefree environment.  I really pray for that child.
